JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Social Development and the South African Social Security Agency (Sassa) have confirmed that all systems are on track for the payment of social grants from 1 April 2017. In a media statement, the department noted that Sassa pay points would not be available for payment on 1 April, as it is a Saturday. Payments would thus occur from 3 April.WATCH: ConCourt rules on Sassa debacleMinister Bathabile Dlamini reassured those qualifying for benefits that they would receive their money as per normal.She also reiterated "her unreserved apology for the anxiety and fear caused about the uncertainty around the payment of social grants. She wished to express her gratitude in advance for the patience and cooperation of South Africa especially the beneficiaries of social grants."READ: Sassa officials nabbed for fraudulent grant payoutsThe statement noted that On 3 April, teams of managers would be deployed to the pay points to provide additional assistance.The following measures would be in place as of 1 April: eNCA